page.title: 18St. George's Estate.
page.content: St George's Estate is situated on La Rue De Cosnets, St. Ouen.It is opposite Les Landes school and St George's church.They are a good example of a typical Jersey estate house built in 1935. When first built there were no bathrooms; 10 yrs after bathrooms were built downstairs. The houses are made of brick, and usually have 1 kitchen and sometimes a dining room. Our house has three bedrooms; some of the other houses have got four or two bedrooms. The houses usually have at least 1 toilet,1 bathroom and 1 lounge. The roofs have brown tiles, the gardens are 22 metres long by 12 metres wide. There is a shed by the gate with one window while at the front of the house there is a garden 1.53 metres long by 1.59 metres wide. The doors are made of wood.
